# CURSOR COMPOSER RULES — Incident Reporting System
 
## WORKFLOW: Plan-Then-Approve (MANDATORY)
 
Before generating ANY code, you MUST:
 
1. Output a numbered PLAN listing all files to be created or modified
2. List the exact functions / components you intend to write
3. STOP and wait for explicit approval ("approved", "proceed", or "yes")
4. Only after approval: generate the code
 
## CONSTRAINTS
 
- Never create files outside the defined project structure
- Never install packages not in the approved dependency list
- Never use class components — functional components with hooks only
- Never use inline styles — Tailwind CSS classes only
- Always add JSDoc comments to every exported function
- Python files must include type hints and docstrings
 
## APPROVED DEPENDENCIES
 
**Frontend:** react, react-dom, vite, @vitejs/plugin-react, tailwindcss, postcss, autoprefixer, axios, uuid, react-router-dom
 
**Backend:** flask, flask-cors, python-dotenv
 
## PROJECT STRUCTURE (SACRED — do not deviate)
 
```
/frontend/src/components/
/frontend/src/pages/
/backend/router.py
/backend/app.py
/data/tickets.json
/docs/README.md
/docs/prompt_log.md
```
 
 
